A ''ribbon'' refers to the mathematical object consisting of a [[Curve]] and an associated 1d unit perpendicular [[Vector field]] on it. Formally it is a pair $$(X,U)$$, of a smooth [[Curve]] $$X$$ together with a smoothly varying Unit [[Vector field]] $$U(t)$$ perpendicular to to $$X$$ (perpendicular to the [[Tangent vector]] of $$X$$). The ribbon is called simple and closed if $$X$$ is [[simple|Simple curve]] and [[closed|Closed curve]] and if $$U$$ and its derivatives agree at $$a$$ and $$b$$. 

